tegory>零售</category><category>批发的</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Georgia Case Presents Unique Challenges for Trump—and Prosecutors]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> RICO 的指控为检察官提供了向陪审团提供全面叙述的机会，但可能被证明难以处理<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001135918"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-835588?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">乔治亚州富尔顿县地方检察官提起的指控称，唐纳德·特朗普参与了推翻 2020 年大选的犯罪活动。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：布林·安德森/美联社</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001135918"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/corinne-ramey" itemprop="url" rel="author">科琳·雷米</a></span>和<span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/james-fanelli" itemprop="url" rel="author">詹姆斯·法内利</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 8 月 15 日下午 4:27（美国东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/georgia-case-presents-unique-challenges-for-trumpand-prosecutors-4dd6ee37"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/donald-trump-indicted-georgia-election-interference-case-64deb461?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">佐治亚州</a>对<a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/donald-trump">唐纳德·特朗普</a>敲诈勒索和其他十几项涉嫌犯罪的起诉是针对这位前总统最雄心勃勃、最全面的案件，并且可能对特朗普和检察官构成前所未有的法律挑战。</p><p>该案件由<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/fani-willis-the-no-nonsense-georgia-prosecutor-on-a-collision-course-with-donald-trump-600b88f8?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">富尔顿县地方检察官法</a>尼·威利斯 (Fani Willis) 提起，指控特朗普<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/who-are-trumps-co-defendants-in-the-georgia-rico-case-73b56354?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">与其他 18 人</a>一起参与犯罪活动，以改变<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/donald-trump-election-grand-jury-georgia-voters-4cd64c0?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">2020 年总统选举</a>对他有利的方式，违反了该州的反敲诈勒索法。</p><p>特朗普否认有不当行为。这位前总统称威利斯有党派倾向，并表示他没有篡改选举。</p><div class="media-object scope-web,mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p>佐治亚州的法律以 1970 年联邦《诈骗影响和腐败组织法》为蓝本，该法为联邦检察官提供了一个新工具，通过将黑帮老大与其犯罪组织内下属的行为联系起来，追捕黑手党。在接下来的几十年里，纽约和其他地方的检察官<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/rudy-giuliani-indicted-racketeering-trump-rico-e2339c94?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">成功地利用联邦 RICO 法</a>打倒了几个著名的黑手党家族和其他犯罪企业。</p><p>佐治亚州的法律在某些方面比联邦版本更广泛，因为它包括更长的基本犯罪清单，可以作为指控一组被告参与共同犯罪活动的基础。</p><p> “佐治亚州的 RICO 法规由于其范围广泛，允许检察官讲述整个故事：人物、事件、时间、地点和方式，”前迪卡尔布县地方检察官、现供职于律师事务所的格温·凯斯·弗莱明 (Gwen Keyes Fleming) 说欧华律师事务所派珀。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=63AF554A-ED80-41F6-BE4D-ADF5F7ECFA84&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fgeorgia-case-presents-unique-challenges-for-trumpand-prosecutors-4dd6ee37&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">前总统唐纳德·特朗普在州和联邦层面面临四项单独的起诉。 《华尔街日报》详细分析了每项起诉书及其对他 2024 年总统竞选的意义。摄影插图：赵安妮<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>特别检察官杰克·史密斯<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/trump-indictment-jack-smith-2020-election-4b351abf?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">最近对特朗普涉嫌寻求推翻 2020 年大选的联邦起诉书</a>与佐治亚州案件有一些相同的主题，但采用了简洁、有针对性的方法。</p><p>相比之下， <a href="https://s.wsj.net/public/resources/documents/GATRUMPINDICTMENT081423.pdf" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noopener">威利斯的起诉书</a>按时间顺序提出了一系列所谓的“行为”，列出了一场巨大而庞大的颠覆选举的阴谋，特朗普被指控在政治上相当于黑帮老大。</p><p> “如果杰克·史密斯对特朗普的严厉控诉是海明威，那么法尼·威利斯对特朗普的控诉则是海明威。</p>布鲁金斯学会高级研究员诺姆·艾森说，这份涵盖 19 名被告、41 条指控的文件就是狄更斯。 “这与所谓的阴谋本身一样庞大和复杂。”<p></p><p>该计划的大量涉嫌参与者也可能给民主党人威利斯带来更多影响力。在典型的 RICO 案件中，检察官经常希望获得一些被告的认罪协议，以换取他们针对最引人注目的目标提供的证词。周一长达 98 页的起诉书表明，检察官已经有了合作证人，其中包括文件中指出的一些未被起诉的同谋者。</p><p>前亚特兰大美国律师兼 King &amp; Spalding 律师事务所合伙人约翰·霍恩 (John Horn) 表示，其他被告最终也可能决定合作，特别是当他们知道如果被定罪就无法立即获得赦免时。 “本案中主要被告面临的风险要大得多，”他说。</p><p>佐治亚州敲诈勒索法的另一个显着特点是：定罪后强制判处最低五年徒刑。</p><p> “如果他被定罪，他就会入狱，”前联邦检察官、亚特兰大刑事辩护律师杰里·弗罗利希 (Jerry Froelich) 说。</p><p>在过去的一些案件中，法官允许被定罪的被告至少部分服刑，而不是入狱服刑。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-835762?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">周一，富尔顿县地方检察官法尼·威利斯在大陪审团对前总统唐纳德·特朗普及其盟友提出起诉后。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：ELIJAH NOUVELAGE/REUTERS</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>如果特朗普赢得下届总统选举，他可能会尝试在任何联邦案件中赦免自己，或引导司法部撤销对史密斯的指控。在佐治亚州，他没有能力消除州定罪或监禁。即使特朗普要寻求州赦免，他也只有在因任何定罪服刑后才有资格这样做。在佐治亚州，任何此类赦免都将由州委员会决定，而不是州长。</p><p>然而，威利斯也面临着挑战。她曾表示，她将寻求在未来六个月内进行审判，但辩护律师表示，这样的时间表可能不切实际。大量被告可能会导致审判安排陷入困境，从而延误任何诉讼程序。由于案件的政治性质和潜在审判的预期时间，陪审团的选择也可能会拖延数月。</p><p>弗吉尼亚州前美国律师小约翰·菲什威克 (John Fishwick Jr.) 表示：“联邦案件更有可能迅​​速进入审判阶段，而不会因多名被告和争论而陷入困境。”他说，乔治亚州的案件“是一个值得推迟的理想案件”。</p><p>另一个悬而未决的案件就说明了这一点。去年，威利斯对与街头暴力团伙有关联的 27 名被告提出了 56 项 RICO 起诉书。一些被告已接受认罪协议，但其余被告的陪审团遴选工作已于一月份开始，预计将再持续一两个月。审判预计需要六到九个月的时间。</p><p>亚特兰大的律师布莱恩·斯蒂尔 (Brian Steel) 代表杰弗里·威廉姆斯 (Jeffery Williams)，他更广为人知的名字是说唱歌手 Young Thug，他是该帮派案件的被告之一。 Steel 表示，RICO 对大量被告的起诉可能在后勤上具有挑战性，而且进展缓慢。他已经代表威廉姆斯对审前动议进行了数周的辩论，还有 50 项动议有待法官审理。 “那只是我，那只是我的客户，”斯蒂尔说。</p><p>特朗普可能会寻求将案件移交联邦法院，进一步推迟诉讼程序。此举需要法官的批准。这位前总统在<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/donald-trump-indictment-new-york-7e64e016?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">纽约的起诉</a>中提出了类似的要求，涉及<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/trumps-hush-money-a-history-of-the-wsjs-investigation-fccf8096?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">向一名色情明星支付封口费</a>。该申请被拒绝，理由是特朗普没有在所谓的封口费计划中履行总统职责。一些律师表示，特朗普可能有更有力的理由推动佐治亚州案件的审理，因为它与总统职位的关系更为直接。</p><p>在联邦法院进行审判对特朗普来说可能是一个优势，因为他可以从更多的县中选择陪审团，其中包括一些倾向于共和党的县。 “在富尔顿县，这是一个相当民主党的县，而且陪审团池非常有限，”弗罗利希说。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-835590?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">在这张法庭素描中，前总统唐纳德·特朗普在本月早些时候的认罪听证会上在联邦法院宣誓，罪名是他策划了一场阴谋，试图推翻自己在 2020 年选举中的失败。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：简·罗森伯格/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>特朗普现已在四起不同案件中被起诉，他于四月份在纽约首次受到指控。曼哈顿地区检察官阿尔文·布拉格 (Alvin Bragg) 指控他犯有 34 项伪造商业记录的重罪，指控他精心策划了一项计划，通过支付封口费来压制可能具有破坏性的性指控，以支持他 2016 年的总统竞选活动。作为初犯，如果在此案中被定罪，他不太可能面临牢狱之灾。</p><p>特朗普<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/trump-associate-also-indicted-in-mar-a-lago-documents-case-759cbb17?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">在六月份受到了他的第一次联邦指控，</a>当时史密斯声称他保留了他知道离开白宫后不应该保留的机密文件。史密斯<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/donald-trump-lawyers-jack-smith-jan-6-58c2fd14" target="_blank" class="icon none">后来补充说</a>，特朗普和他的助手试图删除他的海湖庄园俱乐部的监控录像，以免将其移交给大陪审团。</p><p>特别检察官本月提起了他的另一起更广泛的案件，指控特朗普密谋推翻 2020 年选举结果以继续掌权。</p><p> 2024 年<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/sizing-up-the-2024-republican-primary-field-db34a150" target="_blank" class="icon none">共和党总统提名</a>的领先者特朗普对其他起诉书表示无罪，并指责检察官试图干涉他的选举前景。</p><p>写信给 Corinne Ramey ( <a href="mailto:corinne.ramey@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">corinne.ramey@wsj.com)</a>和 James Fanelli ( <a href="mailto:james.fanelli@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">james.fanelli@wsj.com</a> ) </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/projects/narrator/537f22eb-7442-4360-8305-39f89aae3339.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 15 Aug 2023 20:27:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/georgia-case-presents-unique-challenges-for-trumpand-prosecutors-4dd6ee37</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/georgia-case-presents-unique-challenges-for-trumpand-prosecutors-4dd6ee37<author><![CDATA[Corinne RameyJames Fanelli]]></author><category>特朗普法律</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>犯罪/法律诉讼</category><category>犯罪企业</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>选举</category><category>国家/总统选举</category><category>特朗普法律</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>唐纳德·特朗普</category><category>法尼·威利斯</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>犯罪</category><category>合法举动</category><category>犯罪企业</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>选举</category><category>国家的</category><category>总统选举</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Tesla Launches Cheaper, Lower-Range Model S and Model X]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>汽车制造商在美国推出售价比标准版低 10,000 美元的车型<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001136389"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-835826?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">全球最大的电动汽车制造商特斯拉在经历了艰难的 2022 年之后，今年多次下调了汽车价格。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：斯科特·奥尔森/盖蒂图片社</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001136389"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">通过<span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/alyssa-lukpat" itemprop="url" rel="author">艾莉莎·卢克帕特</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 8 月 15 日上午 11:56 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/tesla-launches-cheaper-lower-range-model-s-and-model-x-f4314fd0"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>据该公司网站称<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/TSLA" class="company-name">，特斯拉</a>发布了其最昂贵的美国汽车 Model S 和 Model X 的廉价版本，价格降低了 10,000 美元，每次充电行驶里程也更少。</p><p>这家电动汽车制造商本周在其网站上推出了所谓的标准续航里程汽车，Model S 售价为 78,490 美元，Model X 售价为 88,490 美元。</p><p>据特斯拉网站称，标准续航里程的 Model S 豪华轿车一次充电可行驶约 320 英里，而普通版则可行驶 405 英里。续航里程较低的 Model X SUV 一次充电的续航里程约为 269 英里，低于普通版本的 348 英里。</p><p>特斯拉<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/tesla-cuts-prices-of-model-x-and-model-s-1898bc5d?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">今年多次</a><a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/tesla-cuts-prices-again-as-it-seeks-to-lure-new-buyers-bc8394e5?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">下调其美国汽车的价格</a>，以刺激竞争激烈的市场需求。首席执行官<a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/elon-musk">埃隆·马斯克</a>表示，一月份的价格下跌<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/tesla-investor-day-2023-elon-musk-3b4e3da0?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">激发了买家的兴趣</a>。部分降价确保其型号的成本低于<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/tesla-nudges-up-model-y-prices-11675532066" target="_blank" class="icon none">联邦税收抵免资格的</a>门槛。</p><p>特斯拉本周也<a href="https://www.wsj.com/livecoverage/stock-market-today-dow-jones-08-14-2023/card/tesla-stock-falls-on-china-price-cuts-local-ev-rivals-also-drop-b05Fe4MNpYQK0gtqyjSw" target="_blank" class="icon none">对中国市场进行了价格调整</a>。这家电动汽车销售商将其两个版本的 Model Y 汽车的价格降幅高达 4.5%，并为其部分新款 Model 3 车辆提供保险子公司。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=B1A79903-5C46-4C69-8AC4-A0082045E182&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Ftesla-launches-cheaper-lower-range-model-s-and-model-x-f4314fd0&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">特斯拉 Cyber​​truck 的推出是历史上最受期待的电动汽车发布之一。巴克莱分析师 Dan Levy 和 AlixPartners 的 Mark Wakefield 探讨了特斯拉首款皮卡将如何撼动市场。照片：弗雷德里克·布朗/盖蒂图片社<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>总部位于德克萨斯州的特斯拉直接向消费​​者销售汽车，无需通过经销商。该公司定期在网上调整价格。与向经销商建议价格的传统汽车制造商相比，特斯拉的定价透明度通常较低。</p><p>全球最大的电动汽车销售商特斯拉在经历了艰难的 2022 年之后，下调了汽车价格。该公司去年公布了<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/tesla-stock-is-headed-for-its-biggest-ever-annual-decline-11672374248" target="_blank" class="icon none">有史以来最糟糕的股票表现</a>，并且<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/elon-musks-tesla-comes-up-short-of-2022-delivery-target-as-growth-slows-11672680081?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">未能达到其车辆交付目标</a>。然而，特斯拉报告称，价格调整后，今年的<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/tesla-deliveries-to-show-whether-price-cuts-are-paying-off-2f2aac93" target="_blank" class="icon none">交付量激增</a>。一些汽车制造商纷纷效仿并降低了价格。</p><p>传统汽车公司已经进入电动汽车市场，但一直难以获得牵引力。<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/GM" class="company-name">通用汽车</a>表示，将在今年年底<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/gms-chevy-bolt-heads-to-scrapyard-with-mixed-legacy-1becc08b?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">逐步淘汰其首款主流电动汽车</a>雪佛兰 Bolt，并推出新版本。<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/F" class="company-name">福特</a>在一月份降低了其<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ford-cuts-prices-of-ev-mustang-mach-e-11675090387" target="_blank" class="icon none">电动野马 Mach-E</a>的价格，随后表示<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ford-projects-3-billion-loss-on-ev-business-for-2023-98037e4e?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">预计今年电动汽车业务将亏损 30 亿美元</a>。</p><p>福特发言人周二表示，该公司今年将扩大电动汽车产量并降低价格，以使电动汽车更容易获得。通用汽车周二拒绝发表评论，并提到了 7 月份有关新款雪佛兰 Bolt 的声明。特斯拉没有立即回复置评请求。</p><p>写信给 Alyssa Lukpat： <a href="mailto:alyssa.lukpat@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">alyssa.lukpat@wsj.com</a></p><p id="correction" class="correction"><strong>更正和放大</strong><br>特斯拉为其部分新款 Model 3 车辆提供保险补贴。本文的早期版本错误地称特斯拉提供了保险子公司。 （8月15日更正） </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/projects/narrator/e1f7a12e-412d-41e7-b6c1-3f6c0615c7c1.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 15 Aug 2023 15:56:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/tesla-launches-cheaper-lower-range-model-s-and-model-x-f4314fd0</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/tesla-launches-cheaper-lower-range-model-s-and-model-x-f4314fd0<author><![CDATA[Alyssa Lukpat]]></author><category> WSJSpeeddesk</category><category>机动车</category><category>乘用车</category><category>替代燃料汽车</category><category>汽车</category><category>新产品/服务</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>产品与服务</category><category>汽车</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>生活/生活方式</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>福特汽车</category><category>F</category><category>特斯拉</category><category>特斯拉</category><category>新产品</category><category>服务</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>产品</category><category>汽车</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>活的</category><category>生活方式</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>机动车</category><category>乘用车</category><category>替代燃料汽车</category><category>汽车</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Americans Flocked to Cancún for Vacation. Now They’re Thinking Twice.]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>这座墨西哥度假城市在 2021 年和 2022 年出现了激增，但游客的优先事项已经发生了变化<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001121949"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="578" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-832622?width=860&amp;height=578" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">在坎昆地区运营的旅游公司正在短期内降低价格。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Elizabeth Ruiz/法新社，盖蒂图片社</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001121949"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/allison-pohle" itemprop="url" rel="author">艾莉森·波尔</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 8 月 15 日上午 10:00 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/cancun-mexico-travel-deals-safety-f5a49403"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>美国游客在阳光下享受乐趣，但他们的思考超越了坎昆等老地方。</p><p>今年春天，美国游客停止了前往坎昆和邻近的里维埃拉玛雅的旅行，将注意力转向<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/american-travelers-are-shunning-the-u-s-for-europe-5b5e08ea?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">欧洲、日本和加勒比海其他地区等目的地</a>。美国商务部国际贸易管理局<a href="https://www.trade.gov/data-visualization/apisi-92-monitor" target="_blank" class="icon none">的数据</a>显示，直飞墨西哥最大度假区坎昆的美国旅客数量与去年同期相比略有下降。酒店和航空公司表示，他们也注意到需求偶尔会下降。</p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p>来自北卡罗来纳州夏洛特的 28 岁内容创作者凯拉·莫里斯 (Khayla Morris) 表示：“我有点厌倦了墨西哥。”莫里斯于 2022 年 5 月与姐妹们一起前往坎昆，并于 2017 年和 2018 年去过坎昆。</p><p>在坎昆地区运营的旅游公司正在降低短期价格，机票价格也较去年有所下降，因为航空公司都押注于长期并增加了航线。</p><h3>寻找其他地方</h3><p><a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/SAVE" class="company-name">Spirit Airlines</a>和 Playa Hotels and Resorts 的高管在最近的财报电话会议上表示，近几个月来坎昆及周边地区的需求出现波动。</p><p> Playa 首席财务官 Ryan Hymel 在公司财报电话会议上表示，这是由于“目的地疲劳”。他在电话中表示，墨西哥是 2021 年和 2022 年的目的地，但由于人们可以前往欧洲或其他加勒比地区旅行，因此不再是优先考虑的地方。 Playa 首席执行官 Bruce Wardinski 表示，游客在旺季有很多选择。</p><p>美国游客仍然喜欢墨西哥。坎昆和里维埃拉玛雅所在地墨西哥金塔纳罗奥州旅游局表示，与 2019 年前六个月相比，1 月至 6 月该地区的美国游客数量增加了约 12%。旅游局表示，这些数字代表了大流行时期增长的放缓，而不是美国游客市场的减少。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="527" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-832869?width=700&amp;height=527" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">近几个月来，更多警察在坎昆巡逻。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：PAOLA CHIOMANTE/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>国际贸易管理局的数据显示，美国飞往坎昆的直达旅客数量在六月和七月有所回升，超过了上年同期。</p><p>许多美国游客在疫情爆发初期<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/a-mexico-vacation-during-the-pandemic-the-rewards-vs-risks-11610655230?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">就选择了墨西哥</a>。与其他主要目的地不同，该国不需要疫苗接种证明或新冠病毒检测呈阴性的证明即可入境。</p><p>墨西哥旅游商业委员会列举了今年春季美国游客数量下降的几个原因，其中包括<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/mexicos-peso-surges-to-strongest-level-since-2015-4286806?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">墨西哥比索升值</a>至近八年来的最高水平，这使得墨西哥对国际游客来说更加昂贵。其他因素包括来自其他目的地的更多竞争以及旅行者对安全的担忧。</p><p>近年来，与毒品有关的暴力导致墨西哥部分地区的凶杀率<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/cancun-tulum-riviera-maya-mexico-drugs-homicides-11648853578?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">达到创纪录水平</a>。近几个月来，更多警察开始在坎昆巡逻。</p><div class="media-object scope-web
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>分享你的意见</h4><p><em>你在坎昆度假吗？为什么或者为什么不？加入下面的对话。</em></p></div></div><p>现代旅游专业公司（Modern Travel Professionals）的老板克里斯汀·哈登伯格（Christine Hardenberger）表示，由于暴力事件的报道，度假者对前往坎昆旅行感到更加焦虑，但许多人最终还是去了那里，因为他们住在以游客为中心的酒店区和里维埃拉玛雅。他们发现，与其他国际目的地相比，他们的花费要多得多，尤其是在全包式度假村。</p><h3>期待便宜货</h3><p>高档 Viceroy Riviera Maya 的销售营销总监图利奥·巴鲁克 (Tulio Baruch) 表示，随着酒店争夺业务，今年秋天游客应该会迎来优惠。</p><p>最大的消费者往往对价格不太敏感。凯悦首席执行官 Mark Hoplamazian 表示，在坎昆里维埃拉玛雅市场，五星级酒店的表现比四星级酒店高出 10 个百分点。他引用了凯悦旗下 ALG Vacations 的数据，该公司是一家度假套餐公司，旗下品牌包括 CheapCaribbean.com 和 Southwest Vacations 等。</p><p>但一些五星级度假村的游客人数有所下降。巴鲁克表示，上季度美国游客在维瑟罗里维埃拉玛雅酒店预订的客房数量比去年同期减少了 15%。他说，度假者选择了意大利、希腊和日本。</p><p>巴鲁克表示，近年来该地区开设了许多新的豪华度假村。他说，需求下降和供应增加意味着酒店必须降低房价。他说，上个季度，前往他的度假村的美国游客每晚支付约 626 美元，比去年同期便宜 45 美元。</p><p>根据旅游搜索引擎 Kayak 的数据，本月飞往坎昆的平均往返经济舱机票价格为 424 美元，比去年下降 10%。</p><p>该航空公司执行副总裁兼首席商务官马特·克莱因 (Matt Klein) 表示，即使价格较高，精神航空 4 月份飞往坎昆的航班也已售空。但他在公司财报电话会议上表示，与去年同期相比，六月份的收入下降了“非常高的两位数”。 “需求刚刚下降，”他说。精神航空降低了票价以解决客流下降的问题。</p><p>许多旅游高管认为需求下降是暂时的，并通过增加航班运力来押注长期利益。美国联合航空公司 (United Airlines) 最近表示，将从 10 月底开始使用大型<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/BA" class="company-name">波音</a>777-200 飞机执飞飞往坎昆的 3 条航线。</p><p>夏洛特的内容创作者莫里斯表示，由于通货膨胀，她正在更加密切地关注自己的资金。她计划今年春天返回坎昆参加婚礼，但会优先考虑其他海滩目的地，例如特克斯和凯科斯群岛。</p><p> “如果我要花这么多钱，我就会去我真正想去的地方，”她说。</p><p><em>订阅新的</em> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/newsletters?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none"><em>《华尔街日报》旅游通讯，</em></a><em>了解《华尔街日报》旅游团队的更多提示和见解。</em></p><p class="articleTagLine"> —<em>安东尼·哈鲁普</em>对本文做出了贡献。</p><p>写信给 Allison Pohle，邮箱为<a href="mailto:allison.pohle@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">allison.pohle@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 15 Aug 2023 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/cancun-mexico-travel-deals-safety-f5a49403</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/cancun-mexico-travel-deals-safety-f5a49403<author><![CDATA[Allison Pohle]]></author><category> WSJ生活工作</category><category>住宿/餐厅/酒吧</category><category>住宿</category><category>酒店/汽车旅馆</category><category>信托/基金/金融工具</category><category>私人产权</category><category>另类投资</category><category>金融服务</category><category>投资/证券</category><category>休闲/艺术/酒店</category><category>旅游</category><category>风险投资</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>消费者优惠</category><category>生活/生活方式</category><category>个人财务</category><category>消费者支出/预算</category><category>旅游优惠/套餐</category><category>旅行</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>内华达普拉亚酒店及度假村</category><category>普拉亚</category><category>凯悦酒店</category><category>H</category><category>精神航空</category><category>节省</category><category>瑞安·海梅尔</category><category>布鲁斯·瓦尔丁斯基</category><category>马克·霍普拉马齐安</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>消费者优惠</category><category>活的</category><category>生活方式</category><category>个人财务</category><category>消费支出</category><category>预算编制</category><category>旅游优惠</category><category>包</category><category>旅行</category><category>住宿</category><category>餐馆</category><category>酒吧</category><category>酒店</category><category>汽车旅馆</category><category>信托</category><category>资金</category><category>金融工具</category><category>私人产权</category><category>另类投资</category><category>金融服务</category><category>投资</category><category>证券</category><category>闲暇</category><category>艺术</category><category>款待</category><category>旅游</category><category>风险投资</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Streamflation Is Here and Media Companies Are Betting You’ll Pay Up]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>迪士尼和其他公司的价格推高是减少损失、引导用户转向更有利可图的广告支持计划的努力的一部分<figure><img src="https://images.wsj.net/im-835516/?width=1278&amp;size=1" alt="左起：Disney+ 的《曼达洛人》、《大楼里的谋杀案》中的史蒂夫·马丁、《龙之屋》中的艾玛·达西。" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><figcaption>左起：Disney+ 的《曼达洛人》、《大楼里的谋杀案》中的史蒂夫·马丁、《龙之屋》中的艾玛·达西。图片插图：戴夫·科尔/《华尔街日报》；照片：Disney+/Lucasfilm/Everett Collection、Hulu/Everett Collection、HBO<span>图片插图：Dave Cole/WSJ；照片：Disney+/Lucasfilm/Everett Collection、Hulu/Everett Collection、HBO</span> </figcaption></figure><!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001134863"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001134863"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/robbie-whelan" itemprop="url" rel="author">罗比·惠兰</a></span>、 <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/joe-flint" itemprop="url" rel="author">乔·弗林特</a></span>和<span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/nate-rattner" itemprop="url" rel="author">内特·拉特纳</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 8 月 15 日上午 9:14（东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/disney-max-hulu-netflix-streaming-price-2c3bac2a"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bigtophero
"></div><p>称之为流通货膨胀。</p><p>据《华尔街日报》分析，观看主要无广告流媒体服务的平均成本在大约一年内上涨了近 25%，因为娱乐巨头押注客户要么付费，要么转向更便宜、更多的服务。利润丰厚的广告支持计划。</p><p>继 Peacock、Max、Paramount+ 和 Apple TV+ 的所有者发布<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/hbo-max-lifts-ad-free-tiers-monthly-price-nearly-7-11673544736?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">一系列类似声明</a>后，<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/DIS" class="company-name">迪士尼</a>上周自去年秋天以来第二次<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/disney-raising-prices-hulu-espn-earnings-call-64ae262?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">提高了其 Disney+ 和 Hulu 流媒体服务的价格</a>。</p><p>最近的价格上涨浪潮标志着流媒体战争进入了新阶段。经过多年的低价定价以追求快速增长后，大多数大型企业都面临着财务清算， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/tvs-golden-era-proved-costly-to-streamers-87353c61?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">数百亿美元的损失不断累积</a>。</p><p>现在，为了提高盈利能力，他们正在测试客户的忠诚度，并押注提高价格不会导致更多的人取消服务，这种行业现象被称为客户流失。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><img width="600" height="976" src="https://s.wsj.net/public/resources/images/34b0fb1c-eb49-422d-bfca-545de493a507-fallback_app.jpg" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p> “你能将价格提高 30% 而不会增加客户流失吗？这是一个大问题，”LightShed Partners 分析师里奇·格林菲尔德 (Rich Greenfield) 表示。</p><p>随着流媒体服务拥有比以往更多的受众，价格上涨。根据周二发布的尼尔森最新数据，流媒体上个月占据了美国人观看时间的创纪录的 38.7%，该数据还显示<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/television-accounts-for-less-than-half-of-u-s-viewing-time-for-the-first-time-158a1fc?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">电视观看时间首次降至 50% 以下</a>。</p><p>流媒体通胀还可能促使更多<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/streaming-data-netflix-hbo-disney-hulu-11643560207?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">人循环订阅和退出订阅</a>——只是为了观看他们最喜欢的节目——并转向带有广告的低成本服务选项。</p><p>当无广告的 Disney+ 服务的每月费用在几周内正式升至 13.99 美元时，该服务的价格将是<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/disney-reports-10-million-users-for-its-new-disney-streaming-service-11573669650?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">2019 年推出价格 6.99 美元的</a>两倍。迪士尼是第一家一年内两次提价的公司。</p><p>迪士尼对一类流媒体平台保持不变： <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/disney-to-roll-out-cheaper-ad-supported-subscription-in-late-2022-11646405231?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">支持广告的 Disney+ 和 Hulu，一旦最新涨价于 10 月 12 日生效，它们将分别比无广告版本</a>便宜 6 美元和 10 美元。</p><p>迪士尼首席执行​​官鲍勃·艾格(Bob Iger)上周在与投资者讨论公司季度业绩的电话会议上表示：“我们显然正在尝试通过定价策略将更多订阅者迁移到广告商支持的层级。”</p><p>近几个月来，迪士尼和包括<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/NFLX" class="company-name">Netflix</a>和 Max 母公司<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/WBD" class="company-name">华纳兄弟探索</a>在内的竞争对手表示，其流媒体平台的广告支持版本比无广告版本为每个用户<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/netflix-reworks-microsoft-pact-lowers-ad-prices-in-bid-for-growth-159b359a?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">带来更多收入</a>，因为广告收入足以抵消较低的订阅收入成本。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><img width="600" height="910" src="https://s.wsj.net/public/resources/images/53666b03-421e-4ca1-b70a-3cf0f173c5a1-fallback_app.jpg" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p> Netflix 在过去一年中因没有提高价格而脱颖而出，上个月停止在美国提供每月 9.99 美元的基本无广告套餐，这大大扩大了其 15.49 美元的标准广告套餐与 15.49 美元的标准广告套餐之间的价格差距。免费计划及其 6.99 美元的广告支持套餐。这家流媒体巨头今年早些时候还<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/netflix-password-sharing-crackdown-families-e5e97e69?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">开始认真限制密码共享</a>，这导致许多家庭必须支付新的月费才能与不与他们住在一起的人共享帐户，这在某种程度上是一种价格上涨。</p><p>总体而言，大多数主要无广告流媒体平台的价格大约是其支持广告的替代品的两倍，Max 是唯一的例外：其无广告套餐每月 15.99 美元，比 9.99 美元的 Max 溢价 60%带有广告。</p><p>其中许多由广告支持的计划还不到一年。最近几个季度，Netflix 和 Disney+ 在北美的订户数量都停滞不前，而提供更实惠的广告支持选项让他们有机会吸引对价格敏感的客户。</p><p>迪士尼表示，自去年底推出带广告的 Disney+ 以来，40% 的新订阅者选择了带有广告的版本。</p><p>在迪士尼的上一轮涨价期间，当该公司为每月 7.99 美元无广告 Disney+ 计划的用户提供保留无广告计划但支付 10.99 美元或继续支付 7.99 美元但接受广告的选项时， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/disney-users-digested-the-streaming-services-recent-price-jump-6dbf637a?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">很少有客户背叛</a>。</p><p>迪士尼表示，大约 94% 的无广告版本订阅者接受了 3 美元的上涨并继续使用该服务。艾格上周表示，这向该公司表明还有进一步提价的空间。迪士尼现在将无广告的 Disney+ 的价格提高到 13.99 美元，而 Hulu 的价格为每月 17.99 美元，即将成为市场上最昂贵的单一流媒体订阅。</p><p>华纳兄弟探索公司首席执行官大卫扎斯拉夫长期以来一直认为，考虑到在内容上的花费<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/david-zaslav-challenged-the-streaming-industrys-orthodoxy-now-rivals-are-following-his-lead-b38dfb1c?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">，大多数流媒体服务的价格都被低估了</a>。 “我们的业务并不是试图吸引每一位订户，我们希望确保我们得到报酬，并且我们得到公平的报酬，” <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/americans-spent-more-time-streaming-than-watching-cable-tv-in-julya-first-11660827184?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">扎斯拉夫去年告诉投资者</a>。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><img width="600" height="832" src="https://s.wsj.net/public/resources/images/9706ff38-f4e3-41f6-8ae5-dd2998a00ae7-fallback_app.jpg" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p>提高价格只是娱乐公司缩小流媒体损失策略的一部分。他们还试图削减开支。</p><p><a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/AMZN" class="company-name">亚马逊</a>前高管罗伊·普莱斯 (Roy Price) 于 2008 年推出了这家零售巨头的点播视频服务，他表示，流媒体正在努力在不牺牲用户增长的情况下削减内容预算。</p><p> “你必须发布足够的内容，在任何特定时期，都有真正好的东西，”他说。 “你需要大量的安打，为了获得这些安打，你必须进行多次击球，”普莱斯说。他表示，流媒体服务应该专注于吸引不断增长的用户群的节目。</p><p> S&amp;P Global Market Intelligence 的数据显示，拥有至少一个流媒体平台的美国家庭平均订阅 4.1 项服务，每月支付 29.64 美元，几乎是 2018 年流媒体战争真正爆发之前的两倍。</p><p>在 2019 年秋季到 2020 年夏季的几个月里，推出了<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-great-streaming-battle-is-here-no-one-is-safe-11573272000?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">四大流媒体服务</a>——Disney+、Peacock、Apple TV+ 以及现在称为 Max 的平台。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bleed
"><img width="600" height="1760" src="https://s.wsj.net/public/resources/images/7b058d84-34ac-4c3e-bed6-10d276f06558-fallback_app.jpg" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p>格林菲尔德表示，鉴于每个平台的成本不断增加，客户在观看完特定节目后在不同<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/streaming-services-deal-with-growing-number-of-subscribers-who-watch-cancel-and-go-11660557601?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">服务之间上下车</a>的风险可能会增加。</p><p> “取消并重新加入流媒体服务非常容易，”他说。 “你可以在 Disney+ 上订阅《曼达洛人》，或者在 Max 上订阅《龙之屋》，然后在看完之后取消。”</p><div class="media-object scope-web
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>分享你的意见</h4><p><em>为了省钱你会放弃哪些流媒体服务？加入下面的对话。</em></p></div></div><p>公司可以部分保护自己免受客户流失影响的一种方法是捆绑流媒体产品。跟踪美国消费者在流媒体服务等产品上的消费习惯的数据提供商 Antenna 长期以来一直指出，迪士尼捆绑包（包括 Disney+、Hulu 和 ESPN+）的流失率一直低于竞争对手。</p><p>迪士尼周三表示，它正在创建一个新的捆绑包，以每月 19.99 美元的价格提供无广告版本的 Disney+ 和 Hulu。</p><p>艾格上周表示，迪士尼的流媒体业务增长得非常快，“甚至在我们了解我们的定价策略应该是什么或可能是什么之前。”</p><p>写信给 Robbie Whelan ( <a href="mailto:robbie.whelan@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">robbie.whelan@wsj.com)</a> 、Joe Flint ( <a href="mailto:Joe.Flint@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">Joe.Flint@wsj.com)</a>和 Nate Rattner ( <a href="mailto:nate.rattner@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">nate.rattner@wsj.com</a> ) </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=0B69A51F-2148-4479-9D5B-1AB9ABE390DC&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fdisney-max-hulu-netflix-streaming-price-2c3bac2a&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption"> Netflix 联席首席执行官特德·萨兰多斯 (Ted Sarandos) 表示，该公司和其他流媒体平台、工作室和网络“非常致力于”与好莱坞知名演员和作家达成协议。照片：克里斯·德尔马斯/法新社/盖蒂图片社<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div></section></div></main></div>]]>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 15 Aug 2023 13:14:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/disney-max-hulu-netflix-streaming-price-2c3bac2a</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/disney-max-hulu-netflix-streaming-price-2c3bac2a<author><![CDATA[Robbie WhelanJoe FlintNate Rattner]]></author><category> WSJ公司</category><category>gfx-contrib</category><category>多媒体内容服务</category><category>广播</category><category>有线广播</category><category>媒体内容分发</category><category>在线服务提供商</category><category>媒体/娱乐</category><category>流媒体服务</category><category>技术</category><category>价格</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>市场/营销</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>华特迪士尼</category><category>DIS</category><category>迪士尼</category><category>价格</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>市场</category><category>营销</category><category>多媒体内容服务</category><category>广播</category><category>有线广播</category><category>媒体内容分发</category><category>在线服务提供商</category><category>媒体</category><category>娱乐</category><category>流媒体服务</category><category>技术</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Television Accounts for Less than Half of U.S. Viewing Time for the First Time]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>尼尔森表示，《金装律师》是上个月收视率最高的流媒体节目<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001135783"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="574" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-835605?width=860&amp;height=574" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> 《金装律师》于 6 月在 Netflix 上线，7 月的观看时长接近 180 亿分钟。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：美国网络/祖玛出版社</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001135783"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/david-marcelis" itemprop="url" rel="author">大卫·马塞利斯</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 8 月 15 日上午 8:33（东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/television-accounts-for-less-than-half-of-u-s-viewing-time-for-the-first-time-158a1fc"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>根据尼尔森的最新数据，在<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/NFLX" class="">Netflix</a>上的《金装律师》等节目的推动下<span class="company-name-type">，</span>流媒体在美国观看时间中所占的份额在 7 月份增长到了新高，而电视观看时间则首次跌破了 50%。</p><p>这一里程碑是<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/disney-max-hulu-netflix-streaming-price-2c3bac2a?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">有线电视捆绑业务迅速受到侵蚀</a>的最新迹象，随着越来越多的美国人放弃有线电视，转而使用 Netflix、谷歌旗下的 YouTube 和<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/DIS" class="">迪士尼</a>等流媒体服务，有线电视捆绑业务在过去十年中流失了约四分之一的订户<span class="company-name-type">。葫芦</span>。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><img width="600" height="880" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-835626?width=600" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p>尼尔森在周二发布的一份新闻稿中表示，7 月份有线电视占美国总收视时间的 29.6%，广播电视则占 20%。与此同时，流媒体服务占据了美国人观看时间的 38.7%，而标记为“其他”的类别（尼尔森表示其中包括 DVD 播放和游戏等使用）则占据了剩余的 11.6%。</p><p>近年来，随着大多数娱乐集团<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/streaming-data-netflix-hbo-disney-hulu-11643560207?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">推出自己的直接面向消费者的服务</a>来与行业领导者 Netflix 抗衡，流媒体平台以牺牲有线电视和广播电视网络为代价的增长速度加快。当他们寻求快速扩大订阅者基础时，他们中的许多人选择仅在流媒体上提供最受瞩目和最昂贵的内容。</p><p>虽然原创内容有助于吸引订阅者并建立流媒体品牌，但观看次数最多的节目有时是较老的电视节目。上个月，美国人花最多时间观看的节目是《金装律师》，这是一部由梅根·马克尔主演的有线电视法律剧，十多年前首播。</p><p>尼尔森表示，该剧于 6 月在 Netflix 上播出，7 月的观看时长接近 180 亿分钟。马克尔<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/britain-puts-on-a-royal-spectacle-for-prince-harry-and-meghan-markles-wedding-1526714332?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">在 2018 年与哈里王子结婚之前</a>退出了节目。 《金装律师》也在<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/CMCSA" class="">康卡斯特</a><span class="company-name-type">的</span>Peacock 上播出。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="394" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-835606?width=700&amp;height=394" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> 《Bluey》在 Disney+ 上表现出色。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：迪士尼+</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> YouTube 是上个月美国观看次数最多的流媒体平台，占总观看时间的 9.2%，而 Netflix 则位居第二，占 8.5%。除了《金装律师》之外，另一部表现出色的流媒体节目是<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/peppa-pig-a-pandemic-favorite-has-american-children-acting-british-11626627266?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">《Bluey》，这是一部在 Disney+ 上播放的关于狗一家人的澳大利亚动画片</a>。</p><p>传统电视的侵蚀正在加速，而流媒体整体使用量自 2022 年 7 月以来增长了四分之一，比去年同期增长了 12%。尼尔森表示，流媒体在总观看次数中所占的份额达到了历史最高水平。</p><p>虽然消费者倾向于大量流媒体，但好莱坞巨头却很难从中赚钱。自从 2020 年左右正式加入流媒体大战以来，娱乐巨头<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/tvs-golden-era-proved-costly-to-streamers-87353c61?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">已经损失了数百亿美元</a>，因为他们在内容上投入巨资，同时为服务收取低廉的价格以追求快速增长。</p><p>在过去一年左右的时间里，许多公司改变了方向，从流媒体平台上删除内容以削减成本，并推出广告支持的服务版本，这让他们有机会扩大吸引力并带来更多收入。</p><p>大多数主播也大幅提高价格。据《华尔街日报》分析，观看主要无广告流媒体服务的平均成本在大约一年内上涨了近 25%，因为公司押注客户要么付费，要么转向更便宜、更有利可图的广告。 - 支持的计划。</p><p>近年来，一些流媒体服务开始提供一些体育赛事直播，这增加了它们的成本，同时进一步威胁到昂贵的付费电视套餐的生存能力。根据标准普尔全球市场情报 (S&amp;P Global Market Intelligence) 的数据，美国家庭平均每月在有线电视上花费约 103 美元。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=0B69A51F-2148-4479-9D5B-1AB9ABE390DC&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Ftelevision-accounts-for-less-than-half-of-u-s-viewing-time-for-the-first-time-158a1fc&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption"> Netflix 联席首席执行官特德·萨兰多斯 (Ted Sarandos) 表示，该公司和其他流媒体平台、工作室和网络“非常致力于”与好莱坞知名演员和作家达成协议。照片：克里斯·德尔马斯/法新社/盖蒂图片社<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>Peacock 和 Apple TV+ 现在独家转播美国职业棒球大联盟的多场比赛，而<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/nfl-regular-season-ratings-fell-amid-thursday-night-football-move-to-amazon-11673391084?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">亚马逊的 Prime Video 已成为国家橄榄球联盟“周四橄榄球之夜”的主要主场</a>。</p><p>即使是通过有线频道提供体育直播获得大量收入的公司也在探索在其流媒体平台上提供这些服务，这是一种平衡之举，因为他们希望在不蚕食其境况不佳的电视网络业务的情况下扩大其流媒体用户群。</p><p><a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/WBD" class="">华纳兄弟探索频道</a><span class="company-name-type">、</span></p> TNT、TBS 和 CNN 有线电视网络以及 Max 流媒体服务的大本营本月早些时候表示，正在努力<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/warner-bros-discovery-wbd-q2-earnings-report-2023-1070dd7d?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">将新闻和体育直播带入其在美国的流媒体服务中。</a>该公司拥有多个知名联赛的体育赛事转播权，其中包括美国篮球协会和美国职业棒球大联盟。<p></p><p>与此同时，迪士尼旗下的 ESPN <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/disneys-espn-plots-its-streaming-future-seeking-tie-ups-with-leagues-and-rivals-25041a41?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">正在寻找战略合作伙伴，以帮助其向流媒体转型</a>。该网络已与潜在合作伙伴和投资者进行了会谈。据《华尔街日报》此前报道，该公司正在努力在两到三年内，或者一旦其在有线电视领域的覆盖率降至 5000 万家庭以下，就向掐线者提供其旗舰电视频道的独立版本。</p><p>大约 7500 万美国家庭仍然订阅付费电视套餐，低于大约十年前约 1 亿的峰值。</p><p>迪士尼首席执行​​官<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/disney-raising-prices-hulu-espn-earnings-call-64ae262?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">鲍勃·艾格上周在讨论公司最新季度收益的电话会议上对投资者表示</a>：“让我们的 ESPN 旗舰频道直接面向消费者不是是否会发生的问题，而是何时发生的问题。”</p><p>写信给大卫·马塞利斯<a href="mailto:david.marcelis@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">david.marcelis@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 15 Aug 2023 12:33:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/television-accounts-for-less-than-half-of-us-viewing-time-for-the-first-time-158a1fc</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/television-accounts-for-less-than-half-of-us-viewing-time-for-the-first-time-158a1fc<author><![CDATA[David Marcelis]]></author><category> WSJ公司</category><category>多媒体内容服务</category><category>广播</category><category>有线广播</category><category>媒体内容分发</category><category>在线服务提供商</category><category>媒体/娱乐</category><category>流媒体服务</category><category>技术</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>艺术/娱乐</category><category>电视/广播</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>艺术</category><category>娱乐</category><category>电视</category><category>收音机</category><category>多媒体内容服务</category><category>广播</category><category>有线广播</category><category>媒体内容分发</category><category>在线服务提供商</category><category>媒体</category><category>流媒体服务</category><category>技术</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Why the White House Went to Wall Street to Revive the U.S. Chips Industry]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>高盛、KKR 和 Blackstone 的人才将帮助确定如何分配 390 亿美元的半导体芯片补贴<figure><img src="https://images.wsj.net/im-833278/?width=3000&amp;size=1.3333333333333" alt="Chips 项目办公室团队的成员包括 Mary Alex Smith、Farha Faisal、Sara O’Rourke 和 Michael Schmidt。" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><figcaption> Chips 项目办公室团队的成员包括 Mary Alex Smith、Farha Faisal、Sara O&#39;Rourke 和 Michael Schmidt。贾里德·苏亚雷斯 (Jared Soares) 供职于《华尔街日报》<span>贾里德·苏亚雷斯 (Jared Soares) 供职于《华尔街日报》</span> </figcaption></figure><!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001122959"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001122959"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/yuka-hayashi" itemprop="url" rel="author">林由香</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 8 月 15 日上午 5:30 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/why-the-white-house-went-to-wall-street-to-revive-the-u-s-chips-industry-fe0a0aac"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bigtophero
"></div><p>华盛顿——为了重振<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chips-semiconductors-manufacturing-china-taiwan-11673650917?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">美国芯片行业</a>，拜登政府发起了二战以来最重大的政府干预行动之一——并且依靠自由市场的大师来实现这一目标。 <strong>&nbsp;</strong>商品。</p><p>自去年夏天两党通过<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chips-act-is-bounty-for-semiconductor-companieswith-many-strings-attached-6e72fd67?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">《芯片与科学法案》</a>以来，商务部一直在悄悄建设<strong>&nbsp;</strong>一个由华尔街精英金融家组成的小团队帮助向数百家公司分配了 390 亿美元的纳税人资助的制造业补贴和其他激励措施。</p><p>团队成员称其为政府内部的初创公司。大约三打专业人士的年龄从 23 岁到 64 岁不等，其中近一半是女性。他们在白宫附近宽敞的商务部大楼外开展业务，房间狭窄，配有钢制家具，隔间之间有高高的隔板。</p><p>拜登政府经常因经济政策<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/bidens-regulatory-drive-sparks-pushback-from-business-lobbyists-11644229802?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">与美国企业发生争执</a>。但在将先进的半导体制造业带回美国时，政府官员表示，他们需要投资银行家、私募股权投资者和管理顾问的技能。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          wrap
"><figure class="media-object-image img-wrap"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="639" height="852" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-833274?width=639&amp;height=852" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">托德·费舍尔 (Todd Fisher) 拥有私募股权背景。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：商务部</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>“Markets don&#39;t always work perfectly,” said <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/commerce-department-names-gatekeeper-of-federal-semiconductor-funds-63d31cc7?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">Todd Fisher</a> , a former executive at private-equity firm <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/KKR" class="company-name">KKR</a> who leads the investment team of the Chips Program Office.</p><p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chips-semiconductors-manufacturing-china-taiwan-11673650917?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">wsj.com/articles/chips-semiconductors-manufacturing-china-taiwan-11673650917(opens in a new tab)</a></p><p> “We are trying to correct a dislocation,” Fisher said, because “other countries put their thumb on the scale.”</p><p> Presidents have long gone to Wall Street to fill top jobs, with Federal Reserve chairman Jay Powell and former Treasury Secretary Steven Mnuchin among the recent examples. But the recruitment of an entire team of private-sector professionals is unprecedented, economists say, and reflects the <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chips-semiconductors-manufacturing-china-taiwan-11673650917?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">central role chips play</a> in modern economies—powering everything <strong>&nbsp;</strong> from household electronics to advanced weapons systems.</p><p> The intensifying <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/pentagon-to-reap-rewards-from-53-billion-chips-act-c3aaa2ca?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">technology and military rivalry</a> with China was the crucial factor in last year&#39;s passage of the Chips Act.</p><p> “The stakes are high and the world is watching,” says John Neuffer, head of the Semiconductor Industry Association. “It&#39;s critical we get this big experiment in industrial policy right for America.”</p><p> The performance of Fisher&#39;s team will be an early test of whether the government can bring back some of the most advanced manufacturing to America&#39;s shores after decades of outsourcing. The US makes only about 10% of global semiconductor supplies and none of the most advanced chips, which are mostly manufactured in Taiwan.</p><p> Some economists are skeptical of industrial policy whereby the government attempts to shape strategic industries using subsidies and tax incentives.</p><p> “Politics always takes over,” said Gary Clyde Hufbauer, a nonresident senior fellow at Peterson Institute for International Economics who has studied US industrial policy.</p><p> The big challenge for the team, he said, is expected pressure from the White House and Congress to steer funds to favored constituencies. As the 2024 election season heats up, he predicts, the program will become “less on chips, and more on creating happy stories for job creation.” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=6F2E219F-28E7-43BF-88B8-CE785ACB359B&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fwhy-the-white-house-went-to-wall-street-to-revive-the-u-s-chips-industry-fe0a0aac&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption"> Illustration: Sharon Shi<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>Commerce Department officials say that the allocation won&#39;t be based on politics and that one reason the government assembled the Wall Street team was to ensure careful rewarding of limited federal resources.</p><p> “We here at the Commerce Department fundamentally have to be good stewards of taxpayer dollars,” said Commerce Secretary Gina Raimondo, who described the team as “unbelievably talented and experienced.”</p><p> The team includes Sara O&#39;Rourke, a former partner at McKinsey &amp; Co., Farha Faisal, who previously worked at private-equity company Blackstone, and former <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/GS" class="company-name">Goldman Sachs</a></p> bankers Kevin Quinn and Srujan Linga. Mary Alex Smith is an investment principal and a former <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/JPM" class="company-name">JPMorgan</a> banker.<p></p><p> The job is to pick winners and losers among some 460 applicants, including top semiconductor companies such as Intel, <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/SSNHZ" class="company-name">Samsung</a> and <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/TSM" class="">Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing</a> <span class="company-name-type">.</span> Their choices will face heavy scrutiny—some of it by members of Congress.</p><p> “In an investment firm, nobody ever knows all the deals you didn&#39;t do,” says Quinn, a senior relationship director who was co-head of global technology banking at Goldman before founding his own investment firm. “Here, you are accountable for all your no&#39;s, and there are a lot of no&#39;s.”</p><p> In Quinn&#39;s cubicle—the first one he&#39;s had since 1994—sits a copy of Chris Miller&#39;s “Chip War.” Required reading for the team, the book examines the geopolitics surrounding semiconductors. <strong>&nbsp;</strong> Team members bought copies <strong><em>&nbsp;</em></strong> at <strong><em>&nbsp;</em></strong> their own expense. Accustomed to private-sector perks, Quinn shrugged his shoulders as he mentioned a requirement to fly coach for work trips to Asia. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-833326?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Commerce Secretary Gina Raimondo stresses the importance of acting as good stewards of taxpayer dollars.</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Evan Vucci/美联社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>With Raimondo—herself a former venture-capital executive—taking a hands-on role, the investment team works similarly to the way that Wall Street deal teams do.</p><p> Each Chips Act grant applicant is assigned a senior relationship director and investment officers. The team&#39;s junior members work long hours crunching numbers to build quantitative models to see whether the projects will pencil out.</p><p> The team must ensure funded projects fulfill President Biden&#39;s political agenda, including promoting a diverse workforce. Some in the chip industry have complained about strings attached to the program&#39;s funding, including <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chip-companies-wary-of-break-with-china-seek-looser-limits-on-federal-cash-cea2067e?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noopener">restrictions on expansion in China</a> , limits on executive compensation, and mandatory daycare for workers&#39; children.</p><p> The investment team works closely with officials specializing in Biden strategies, including defense experts and economists. Investment team members report to Michael Schmidt, director for the Chips Program Office and a former New York state official. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          wrap
"><figure class="media-object-image img-wrap"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="639" height="852" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-833273?width=639&amp;height=852" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Srujan Linga took a huge pay cut to join the team.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Department of Commerce</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> Officials won&#39;t say when Chips Act funds will be awarded, but industry executives expect it could be as soon as late this year.</p><p> “We are literally designing the strategy, designing the organization and designing the investment process as we go,” said <strong>&nbsp;</strong> O&#39;Rourke, the team&#39;s operations chief.</p><p> The initial allocation will be just a first step. Compared with the industry&#39;s long-term investment needs, the $39 billion in manufacturing incentives is a “rounding error,” says Stacy Rasgon, a senior analyst at Bernstein Research.</p><p> TSMC plans to spend $40 billion to build new <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/tsmc-delays-start-of-first-arizona-chip-factory-citing-worker-shortage-4a9344e5" target="_blank" class="icon none">advanced plants in Arizona</a> . The industry needs to spend $3 trillion globally in research and equipment over the next decade to meet the demand for chips, according to a Boston Consulting Group estimate.</p><p> “We will not be successful if we don&#39;t find ways to use our money to incentivize private capital,” Fisher said.</p><p> That task falls heavily on Linga, who leads the team&#39;s financial structuring group. As a top banker specializing in asset-backed financing at Goldman, he helped <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/united-to-put-up-frequent-flier-program-for-5-billion-loan-11592227825?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">airlines borrow</a> by using frequent-flier programs as collateral and Sprint issue debt backed by wireless spectrum licenses.</p><div class="media-object scope-web
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>分享你的意见</h4><p><em>How do you think the public-private partnership will work to revive the US chip industry?加入下面的对话。</em></p></div></div><p> An Indian immigrant who traded a $5 million annual paycheck for a $183,500-a-year government job, Linga said he realized <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/pentagon-to-reap-rewards-from-53-billion-chips-act-c3aaa2ca?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">the national security implications</a> at stake when he bumped into an army general at Raimondo&#39;s office during his job interview. “When the US government offers you a role like this, it&#39;s an honor,” he said.</p><p> Linga is looking for ways semiconductor suppliers <strong>&nbsp;</strong> can raise money from pension funds and insurance companies. To make lending more attractive, he says, loans can be secured by the value of equipment, intellectual property and infrastructure.</p><p> Some team members, including investment director Faisal, who used to work at Blackstone, say America&#39;s reliance on foreign-made chips has become an Achilles&#39; heel, justifying government intervention—for now. Longer term, they say, the aim is to build an industry that can fund its own growth.</p><p> “We are going to do this because we want to spur the private sector to come in,” Faisal said.</p><p> Write to Yuka Hayashi at <a href="mailto:Yuka.Hayashi@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">Yuka.Hayashi@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 15 Aug 2023 09:30:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/why-the-white-house-went-to-wall-street-to-revive-the-us-chips-industry-fe0a0aac</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/why-the-white-house-went-to-wall-street-to-revive-the-us-chips-industry-fe0a0aac<author><![CDATA[Yuka Hayashi]]></author><category>摄影委托</category><category>半导体</category><category>银行业</category><category>Trusts/Funds/Financial Vehicles</category><category>私人产权</category><category>金融投资服务</category><category>Security Brokering/Dealing</category><category> Alternative Investments</category><category>银行/信贷</category><category>金融服务</category><category>工业电子</category><category>工业品</category><category>Integrated Circuits</category><category>投资/证券</category><category>技术</category><category>法规/政府政策</category><category>政府援助/赠款</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>规定</category><category>政府政策</category><category>政府援助</category><category>赠款</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>半导体</category><category>银行业</category><category>trusts</category><category>资金</category><category>financial vehicles</category><category> private equity</category><category>金融投资服务</category><category>security brokering</category><category> dealing</category><category> alternative investments</category><category>信用</category><category>金融服务</category><category>工业电子</category><category>工业品</category><category>integrated circuits</category><category>投资</category><category>证券</category><category>技术</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Tesla Alums Win Big in Green Energy Bonanza]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> Executives who survived EV maker&#39;s dark days have raised billions from investors <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001129914"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="700" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-834626?width=700&amp;height=700" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCredit"> Illustration: Alexandra Citrin-Safadi/The Wall Street Journal </p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001129914"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/ed-ballard" itemprop="url" rel="author">Ed Ballard</a></span> and <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/amrith-ramkumar" itemprop="url" rel="author">Amrith Ramkumar</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> Aug. 15, 2023 5:30 am ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/tesla-alums-win-big-in-green-energy-bonanza-33d63414"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p> Governments everywhere are trying to build domestic clean-energy industries, from electric cars to solar panels. No company has had more recent success doing that than <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/TSLA" class="">Tesla</a> <span class="company-name-type">,</span> and no executives are in greater demand than the auto maker&#39;s alumni.</p><p> More than 30 companies led or launched by former Tesla employees have raised more than $26 billion in the past decade, most in the past few years, a Wall Street Journal analysis of data from PitchBook shows. Much of that money went to a handful of companies in the electric-car and battery supply chain: luxury electric-vehicle company <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/LCID" class="">Lucid Group</a> <span class="company-name-type">,</span> European battery upstart Northvolt and battery-recycling firm Redwood Materials.</p><p> Many of these companies focus on domestic manufacturing, as Tesla has for more than a decade. They are well-positioned to take advantage of <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-biggest-winners-in-americas-climate-law-foreign-companies-c672e09d?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">last year&#39;s US climate law</a> and Europe&#39;s response to it. A key goal for both is to whittle away at China&#39;s dominance in critical clean-energy industries.</p><p> The Tesla diaspora continues a pattern established earlier in Chief Executive <a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/elon-musk">Elon Musk</a> &#39;s career. He is part of the so-called <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-shadow-crew-who-encouraged-elon-musks-twitter-takeover-tesla-jack-dorsey-11651260119?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">PayPal mafia</a> , the group of technology-industry power brokers who came out of the digital-payments company.</p><p> Former Tesla executives say their experience ramping up manufacturing of Tesla&#39;s Model 3, an existential event for the company, gives them credibility with investors. Some of them say they swap notes on growth and fundraising.</p><p> “We used to joke that if you could survive Model 3 &#39; <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/elon-musks-trip-through-hell-inside-the-2018-scramble-to-avoid-the-collapse-of-tesla-11627660800?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">manufacturing hell</a> ,&#39; you can survive anything,” said Vivas Kumar, CEO of battery-parts upstart Mitra Chem.</p><p> Here is a look at some notable clean-energy executives who previously worked at Tesla and how much money they have raised: </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          edgetoedge
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/projects/narrator/972d8518-572b-4eea-a863-d92b82e8c6fd.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 15 Aug 2023 09:30:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/tesla-alums-win-big-in-green-energy-bonanza-33d63414</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/tesla-alums-win-big-in-green-energy-bonanza-33d63414<author><![CDATA[Ed BallardAmrith Ramkumar]]></author><category> wsjclimate</category><category> wsjfinance-rer</category><category> Energy</category><category>电池</category><category>机动车</category><category>替代燃料汽车</category><category>汽车</category><category>工业电子</category><category>工业品</category><category>技术</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category> Lucid Group</category><category> LCID</category><category> Tesla</category><category> TSLA</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>energy</category><category>电池</category><category>机动车</category><category>替代燃料汽车</category><category>汽车</category><category>工业电子</category><category>工业品</category><category>技术</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Donald Trump Indicted in Georgia Over Effort to Overturn Election Results]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> Charges brought by Fulton County&#39;s district attorney mark fourth criminal case against former president <figure><img src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831598/?width=1278&amp;size=1" alt="2024 年共和党总统提名的领跑者、前总统唐纳德·特朗普否认有不当行为。" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><figcaption> Former President Donald Trump, the front-runner for the 2024 Republican presidential nomination, denies wrongdoing. Melissa Sue Gerrits/Getty Images <span>Melissa Sue Gerrits/Getty Images</span> </figcaption></figure><!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001116987"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001116987"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/cameron-mcwhirter" itemprop="url" rel="author">Cameron McWhirter</a></span> , <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/jan-wolfe" itemprop="url" rel="author">Jan Wolfe</a></span> , <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/aruna-viswanatha" itemprop="url" rel="author">Aruna Viswanatha</a></span> and <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/sadie-gurman" itemprop="url" rel="author">Sadie Gurman</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> Updated Aug. 15, 2023 1:22 am ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/donald-trump-indicted-georgia-election-interference-case-64deb461"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bigtophero
"></div><p> ATLANTA—A grand jury here charged <a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/donald-trump">Donald Trump</a> , Rudy Giuliani and other Trump allies with operating a criminal enterprise that sought to overturn <a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/joe-biden">Joe Biden</a> &#39;s electoral victory in Georgia, marking the fourth time the <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/a-guide-to-donald-trumps-legal-perils-b9b64891?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">former president has been indicted</a> this year and <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-new-charges-facing-donald-trump-and-how-he-might-defend-himself-53a2b45?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">deepening his legal woes</a> ahead of the 2024 election.</p><p> There were 19 people in total <a href="https://s.wsj.net/public/resources/documents/GATRUMPINDICTMENT081423.pdf" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noopener">charged in the indictment</a> , including former Trump White House chief of staff Mark Meadows and legal adviser Sidney Powell.</p><p> Taken together, the Georgia charges allege a sweeping criminal conspiracy to overturn the 2020 election result and undermine US democracy. They describe calls, emails, and other efforts to allegedly press state and federal officials into backing the effort to find votes Trump lacked to win or assert that he was victorious both in Georgia and other states he lost.</p><p> The sprawling indictment, <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/fani-willis-the-no-nonsense-georgia-prosecutor-on-a-collision-course-with-donald-trump-600b88f8?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">brought by</a> Fulton County District Attorney Fani Willis, covers some of the same ground as the federal case Trump faces in Washington, but goes into greater detail on the effort in Georgia and offers some new elements of the alleged conspiracy. It charges Trump with 13 felonies, alleging he pushed false claims of voter fraud in Georgia and pressured Republican officials to help him secure the state&#39;s Electoral College votes. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=63AF554A-ED80-41F6-BE4D-ADF5F7ECFA84&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fdonald-trump-indicted-georgia-election-interference-case-64deb461&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption"> Former president Donald Trump is facing four separate indictments at both state and federal levels. 《华尔街日报》详细分析了每项起诉书及其对他 2024 年总统竞选的意义。摄影插图：赵安妮<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>Willis, whose investigation lasted more than two years, used the state&#39;s sweeping antiracketeering law to describe an elaborate plot to stay in power over the will of Georgia voters. Biden narrowly won the state in 2020.</p><p> “The defendants engaged in a criminal racketeering enterprise to overturn Georgia&#39;s presidential election results,” Willis said during a press conference late Monday, adding that the defendants pursued an illegal goal of allowing Trump to seize a presidential term.</p><p> She said she would seek a trial date in the next six months. She gave the defendants until Friday, Aug. 25, to turn themselves in.</p><p> Trump, on his Truth Social platform, declared the investigation a witch hunt. “他们为什么不在 2.5 年前起诉？ Because they wanted to do it right in the middle of my political campaign,” he said.</p><p> Trump&#39;s lawyers issued a statement that said in part, “We look forward to a detailed review of this indictment which is undoubtedly just as flawed and unconstitutional as this entire process has been.” </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><img width="600" height="896" src="https://s.wsj.net/public/resources/images/a7dc45f6-d690-4f27-9034-c24e2929ee1d-fallback_app.jpg" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p> The indictment details 161 separate acts it says were undertaken as part of the conspiracy to reverse the election outcome, beginning with a speech Trump gave declaring victory the day after the presidential election. It also alleges that the criminal enterprise operated in Georgia outside of Fulton County as well as in other states, including Michigan, Arizona, Pennsylvania, Nevada and New Mexico.</p><p> The indictment alleges Giuliani led the effort in battleground states, including Georgia, to keep Trump in power. Giuliani called the indictment “an affront to American Democracy” and said it does “permanent, irrevocable harm to our justice system.”</p><p> Several individuals are charged with breaching voting machines in Coffee County, a rural county about 200 miles from Atlanta. Those defendants, including Powell, were charged with conspiracy to commit computer theft. Powell had pushed false claims that voting machines had been hacked to flip votes from Trump to Biden.</p><p> Willis also indicted John Eastman and Kenneth Chesebro, who argued in legal memos that then-Vice President <a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/mike-pence">Mike Pence</a> could block Electoral College votes from being certified.</p><p> Other defendants include Jenna Ellis, a former Trump lawyer, and</p> Jeffrey Clark, a Trump administration Justice Department official who urged his colleagues to launch investigations in Georgia based on Trump&#39;s unsupported claims of voting fraud. A lawyer for Ellis didn&#39;t immediately return calls for comment.<p></p><p> “ Jeff Clark was simply doing his job in 2020 and he doesn&#39;t deserve to be subjected to this naked political lawfare, especially not by a publicity hound like Willis,” said Rachel Cauley, a spokeswoman for Center for Renewing America, the conservative think tank where Clark works. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=1F164012-9314-4C51-AF75-113013B9D8A3&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fdonald-trump-indicted-georgia-election-interference-case-64deb461&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption"> Fulton County District Attorney Fani Willis announced 41 counts against former President Donald Trump and 18 other people for operating a criminal enterprise that sought to overturn the 2020 election in Georgia. Photo: John Bazemore/Associated Press<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>Lawyers for Eastman, Meadows, Chesebro and Powell didn&#39;t immediately respond to requests for comment.</p><p> Three other defendants charged were “fake electors” or “alternate electors,” individuals who signed a certificate falsely stating that Trump had won Georgia in the 2020 election and declared themselves the state&#39;s “duly elected and qualified” electors.</p><p> Elsewhere, political reaction split along usual partisan lines.</p><p> House Speaker Kevin McCarthy (R., Calif.) in a tweet late Monday accused Willis of attacking Trump to advance her own political career.</p><p> Rep. Elise Stefanik of New York, a member of House GOP leadership, said: “President Trump had every legal right to challenge the results of the election” and accused Willis of bias.</p><p> Rep. Nikema Williams (D., Ga.), who also serves as chair of Georgia Democrats, said Trump had assaulted democracy by trying to disenfranchise Georgia voters because he didn&#39;t like the result of the 2020 election. “Now, Donald Trump is facing the consequences of his actions,” Williams said.</p><p> The indictment also charged several of the defendants with filing false documents, in some cases by sending the false elector certificates, and, in the case of Trump and Eastman, by filing a New Year&#39;s Eve lawsuit in federal court that included alleged lies such as that thousands of minors and dead people voted in the 2020 election.</p><div class="media-object scope-web,mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p> In addition to the 19 defendants, the indictment describes a further 30 people as unindicted co-conspirators, leaving open the possibility of additional charges in connection with the case.</p><p> The move by Willis, a Democrat, had been widely anticipated. In April, she said she planned to announce charging decisions this summer, and she had told local law-enforcement leaders to prepare for the “significant public reaction” her announcement could trigger.</p><p> Willis opened the probe on the basis of a recorded Jan. 2, 2021, phone call in which then-President Trump urged Republican Brad Raffensperger, Georgia&#39;s top elections official, to find enough votes to overturn the election. Trump, the front-runner for the 2024 Republican presidential nomination, denies wrongdoing and has said the call was perfect.</p><p> Willis convened a special grand jury, which heard from more than 75 witnesses, wrote a report summarizing its findings and recommended criminal charges against several people whose identities haven&#39;t been made public. The special grand jury lacked the authority to issue indictments, however, prompting Willis to present evidence to a regular grand jury.</p><p> In November 2020, Trump lost the election in Georgia to Biden by roughly 12,000 votes out of five million cast. Trump and his supporters claimed the election was stolen, but statewide recounts and a partial forensic audit overseen by state election officials found no evidence of widespread fraud. Court challenges failed. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831333?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> The indictment brought by Fulton County District Attorney Fani Willis alleges the former president pushed false claims of voter fraud and pressured Republican officials to help him secure Georgia&#39;s Electoral College votes.</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：布林·安德森/美联社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>The Monday indictment also outlines multiple episodes involving Meadows, who was the White House chief of staff when Trump tried to overturn the 2020 election result. Meadows featured minimally in the federal election-interference case and wasn&#39;t identifiable as one of the six unindicted co-conspirators in that case, where Trump is the only defendant.</p><p> The new indictment levels two charges against Meadows related to the alleged conspiracy, saying he attended meetings where Trump allegedly brought up lies about election fraud and he worked to arrange Trump calls with state officials to further the efforts, including the call during which Trump asked Georgia officials to find him more votes.</p><p> The indictment also describes a meeting at which Trump and Meadows allegedly asked Trump aide John McEntee to prepare a memo on how to disrupt or delay Congress&#39;s Jan. 6 counting of the electoral votes. And it charges both Trump and Meadows with trying to get Raffensperger to violate his oath of public office by pressuring him to change the results there.</p><p> Earlier this year, Trump was indicted by Manhattan District Attorney Alvin Bragg over the payment of <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/grand-jury-votes-to-indict-donald-trump-a9512240?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">hush money to a porn star</a> on the eve of the 2016 election, marking the first time a former president has <a href="https://www.wsj.com/livecoverage/donald-trump-indictment-arrest-da-bragg?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">faced criminal charges</a> .</p><div class="media-object scope-web
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>分享你的意见</h4><p><em>How will the latest charges against Donald Trump play out?加入下面的对话。</em></p></div></div><p> Then in June, federal prosecutors led by special counsel Jack Smith unsealed <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-federal-case-against-trump-on-the-mar-a-lago-documents-12054f5?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">a sweeping indictment</a> alleging the former president <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/donald-trump-indicted-in-document-case-b4e563d7?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">held on to classified documents</a> he knew he shouldn&#39;t have retained access to, shared them with others and directed his staff to help him evade authorities&#39; efforts to get them back. The case is being handled in Florida.</p><p> A superseding federal indictment returned in late July charged Trump with three additional counts, including one of willful <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/donald-trump-lawyers-jack-smith-jan-6-58c2fd14?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">retention of national-defense information</a> , stemming from a classified national-security document prosecutors said he showed to visitors at his golf club in New Jersey.</p><p> Trump was indicted a third time Aug. 1 in a further criminal case accusing him of trying to subvert the will of American voters through his attempts to cling to power after he lost the 2020 election. <a href="https://s.wsj.net/public/resources/documents/trumpindictment080123.pdf" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noopener">That indictment</a> , by a federal grand jury in Washington, <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-new-charges-facing-donald-trump-and-how-he-might-defend-himself-53a2b45?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">charges Trump with four crimes</a> , including conspiring to defraud the US, obstructing an official proceeding and conspiring against the rights of voters by his actions that culminated in the Jan. 6, 2021, <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-protesters-are-in-the-building-inside-the-capitol-stormed-by-a-pro-trump-mob-11609984654?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">attack by his supporters</a> on the US Capitol.</p><p> Trump pleaded not guilty in the New York, Florida and Washington, DC, cases. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/projects/narrator/537f22eb-7442-4360-8305-39f89aae3339.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div><p class="articleTagLine"> —Byron Tau, Alex Leary, Lindsay Wise and Isaac Yu contributed to this article.</p><p> Write to Cameron McWhirter at <a href="mailto:Cameron.McWhirter@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">Cameron.McWhirter@wsj.com</a> , Jan Wolfe at <a href="mailto:jan.wolfe@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">jan.wolfe@wsj.com</a> , Aruna Viswanatha at <a href="mailto:aruna.viswanatha@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">aruna.viswanatha@wsj.com</a> and Sadie Gurman at <a href="mailto:sadie.gurman@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">sadie.gurman@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 15 Aug 2023 05:22:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/donald-trump-indicted-georgia-election-interference-case-64deb461</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/donald-trump-indicted-georgia-election-interference-case-64deb461<author><![CDATA[Cameron McWhirterJan WolfeAruna ViswanathaSadie Gurman]]></author><category>特朗普法律</category><category>华尔街日报-美国新闻</category><category>gfx-contrib</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>犯罪/法律诉讼</category><category>犯罪企业</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>选举</category><category>国家/总统选举</category><category>特朗普法律</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>犯罪</category><category>合法举动</category><category>犯罪企业</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>选举</category><category>国家的</category><category>总统选举</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Wall Street Is Ready to Scoop Up Commercial Real Estate on the Cheap]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> Firms are raising billions of dollars for funds to target assets with slumping values <figure><img src="https://images.wsj.net/im-833597/?width=1278&amp;size=1" alt="Vacancy rates in the office market have soared amid a sluggish return-to-the-office pace." referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><figcaption> Vacancy rates in the office market have soared amid a sluggish return-to-the-office pace. BRENDAN MCDERMID/REUTERS <span>BRENDAN MCDERMID/REUTERS</span> </figcaption></figure><!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001133014"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001133014"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/peter-grant" itemprop="url" rel="author">Peter Grant</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> Updated Aug. 15, 2023 12:00 am ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/wall-street-is-ready-to-scoop-up-commercial-real-estateon-the-cheap-6edac64f"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bigtophero
"></div><p> Wall Street firms are raising new funds to acquire <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-return-to-the-office-has-stalled-e0af9741?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">office buildings</a> , apartments and other troubled commercial real estate, looking to scoop up properties at a fraction of the price investors paid a few years ago.</p><p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/CNS" class="">Cohen &amp; Steers</a> <span class="company-name-type">,</span> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/GS" class="">Goldman Sachs</a> <span class="company-name-type">,</span> EQT Exeter and BGO, formerly known as BentallGreenOak, are among the prominent names raising billions of dollars for funds to target distressed assets and other real estate with slumping values, according to regulatory filings.</p><p> “The last few weeks, I&#39;ve been saying, &#39;holy mackerel, they&#39;re coming out of the woodwork,&#39;” said Kevin Gannon, chief executive of Robert A. Stanger &amp; Co., an investment-banking firm that tracks real-estate fundraising. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=88CDF171-D046-4FD4-A4BB-72130DCCB4C6&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fwall-street-is-ready-to-scoop-up-commercial-real-estateon-the-cheap-6edac64f&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption"> With housing in short supply, developers are converting more empty offices into apartments. But not all buildings are candidates for reuse, even as more than one billion square feet of office space sits vacant across the US Photo Illustration: Amber Bragdon<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>The new funds are seeking to capitalize on one of the most troubled commercial-property markets in decades. Values have nosedived since interest rates spiked last year, driving up borrowing costs in the highly leveraged business. The office market, one of the largest sectors, has also been clobbered by a sluggish return-to-office rate, which has sent vacancy rates soaring. <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/a-real-estate-haven-turns-perilous-with-roughly-1-trillion-coming-due-74d20528?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">Apartment buildings</a> , an investor haven in the past, look vulnerable as owners try to refinance at much higher rates. <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/local-malls-stuck-in-death-spiral-plunge-in-value-a7998b7d?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">Mall owners are contending with</a> steep value declines, some of more than 70% over the past few years.</p><p> Commercial-property sales have been moribund until recently because most sellers haven&#39;t been willing to cut their prices to the levels that buyers are demanding. Now, a small but growing number of <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/rise-in-distressed-sales-signals-new-chapter-for-beleaguered-office-market-bbff313c?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">office owners have begun to capitulate</a> , unloading distressed properties.</p><p> The capitulation marks a new phase in the commercial real-estate upheaval, as more beleaguered property owners turn over properties to lenders or decide to take what they can get, rather than hold out hope for an eventual recovery. This wave of fundraising is the latest sign that sales activity is expected to increase as more sellers yield on price. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          wrap
"><figure class="media-object-image img-wrap"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="639" height="827" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-834573?width=639&amp;height=827" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Developer Presidio Bay purchased a San Francisco office tower for $41 million, compared with its 2014 sales price of $107 million.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Jeff Peters</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> In one recent example, the owner of a downtown San Francisco office tower unloaded the property for $41 million to developer Presidio Bay. The seller, Clarion Partners, had purchased the property for $107 million in 2014.</p><p> While the clearest distress is in the office sector, many property owners with floating-rate debt may also feel pressured to sell at marked-down prices because they are unable to refinance at today&#39;s higher rates. In addition, fund managers expect values to fall as regional banks, under pressure from this year&#39;s <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/bank-collapse-crisis-timeline-724f6458?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">rash of bank failures</a> , unload commercial-property loan portfolios at discounted prices.</p><p> “There are selective opportunities beginning to arise for investors that are in a position to take advantage of weakness,” said Rich Hill,</p> head of real-estate strategy for Cohen &amp; Steers, which is aiming to raise more than $2.5 billion in a new nontraded real-estate investment trust.<p></p><p> Commercial-property values already have fallen about 10 to 15 percentage points from their peaks in the third quarter last year, and might fall a total of 20 to 25 percentage points, said Hill. “You have to go back to the [savings and loan] crisis and the global financial crisis to see such big declines in property valuations,” he said.</p><p> The volume of distressed commercial real estate grew by $8 billion in the second quarter, reflecting the rise in cases where the owners defaulted or lenders foreclosed, according to data provider MSCI Real Assets. That is the biggest quarterly increase since the second quarter of 2020.</p><p> While most of the new funds are looking to buy property, some are planning to lend to property owners and fill the void left by the <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/new-lending-by-mortgage-reits-has-dried-up-49551878?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">cutback in activity</a> from regional banks and mortgage real-estate investment trusts. With less competition, the lenders who are still active are able to charge higher rates and get better deal terms from borrowers.</p><p> Invesco Real Estate, which has a long track record of raising funds from institutional investors for real-estate credit funds, is raising its first such fund targeting the retail audience.</p><div class="media-object scope-web
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>分享你的意见</h4><p><em>Is commercial real estate undervalued right now?为什么或者为什么不？加入下面的对话。</em></p></div></div><p> Many of the new funds, such as those being raised by Invesco and Cohen &amp; Steers, are targeting individual investors. Smaller investors have shown an enormous appetite for property investments in recent years, especially with the growth of the nontraded real-estate investment trust industry which raised about $100 billion in the past seven years.</p><p> But many of the nontraded REITs that were formed before last year&#39;s rise in interest rates have been under pressure to redeem money back to investors who want to cash out. Over $9 billion was redeemed in the first six months of this year, according to Stanger, and many investors have been forced to wait to get their money because of the rush to the redemption door.</p><p> Still, the new funds will be facing a lot of competition from cash-rich funds aimed at institutions. Opportunistic real-estate funds run by private-equity firms have nearly $145 billion in so-called dry powder for future investments, up from $120 billion at the end of last year, according to data firm Preqin.</p><p> It is still possible that distressed opportunities won&#39;t arise if the US economy has <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/what-top-executives-are-saying-about-a-soft-landing-4daf9123?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">a soft landing</a> , in which inflation is tamed by the Federal Reserve without tipping the economy into recession.</p><p> Sales volume will likely increase when debt markets stabilize and values become more clear. “Broadly speaking, people are waiting to see what the world looks like,” said Michael Stark, co-head of the PJT Park Hill Real Estate Group, a global advisory firm and placement agent. “They&#39;re waiting for motivated sellers.”</p><p> Write to Peter Grant at <a href="mailto:peter.grant@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">peter.grant@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 15 Aug 2023 04:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/wall-street-is-ready-to-scoop-up-commercial-real-estateon-the-cheap-6edac64f</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/wall-street-is-ready-to-scoop-up-commercial-real-estateon-the-cheap-6edac64f<author><![CDATA[Peter Grant]]></author><category> commercial re</category><category> Marine Transport</category><category> Trusts/Funds/Financial Vehicles</category><category> Investment Trusts</category><category> Real Estate Investment Trusts</category><category> Real Estate Services/Transactions</category><category> Freight Transport/Logistics</category><category> Commercial/Industrial Real Estate</category><category>房地产/建筑</category><category>金融服务</category><category>投资/证券</category><category>Marine Freight</category><category>房地产</category><category>Water Transport/Shipping</category><category> Transportation/Logistics</category><category> Ownership Changes</category><category> Physical Asset Transactions</category><category> Corporate Actions</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>Commercial RE</category><category> SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category> Cohen &amp; Steers</category><category> CNS</category><category> Goldman Sachs</category><category> GS</category><category> EQT Exeter</category><category> ownership changes</category><category> physical asset transactions</category><category> corporate actions</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>marine transport</category><category> trusts</category><category>资金</category><category>financial vehicles</category><category> investment trusts</category><category> real estate investment trusts</category><category> real estate services</category><category> transactions</category><category> freight transport</category><category> logistics</category><category> commercial</category><category> industrial real estate</category><category>房地产</category><category>建造</category><category>金融服务</category><category>投资</category><category>证券</category><category>marine freight</category><category> water transport</category><category> shipping</category><category> transportation</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Amazon’s Leader on Alexa, Other Devices Plans to Leave]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>大卫·林普 (David Limp) 的退休将是电子商务巨头首席执行官安迪·贾西 (Andy Jassy) 领导下的最新一次离职<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001134161"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-835255?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> David Limp 于 20 世纪 80 年代末在 Apple 开始了他的职业生涯，随后在其他几家公司工作过，之后加入 Amazon 运营其设备部门。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：《华尔街日报》的安迪·戴维斯</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001134161"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/dana-mattioli" itemprop="url" rel="author">达纳·马蒂奥利</a></span>和<span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/jessica-toonkel" itemprop="url" rel="author">杰西卡·图恩克尔</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 8 月 14 日下午 4:04（美国东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/amazons-leader-on-alexa-echo-and-other-devices-plans-to-leave-cde4f689"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p><a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/AMZN" class="">亚马逊</a><span class="company-name-type">设备</span>主管戴维·林普(David Limp)计划在未来几个月内退休，这是自两年前安迪·贾西(Andy Jassy)接任这家电子商务巨头首席执行官以来，长期担任高管的最新一次离职。</p><p>林普的离职计划将结束他在公司超过 13 年的任期，他负责监管亚马逊的 Alexa 以及一系列其他<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ftc-amazons-ring-reach-5-8-million-settlement-on-alleged-privacy-violations-8b674923?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">服务和小工具</a>，这些服务和小工具在某些情况下很受欢迎，但总体来说却<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/amazon-amzn-q1-earnings-report-2023-cb206c2a?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">很难赚钱</a>。熟悉 Limp 计划的人士表示，事实证明，以这种方式实现盈利尤其具有挑战性，尤其是 Echo 设备系列。</p><p> Limp 的部门一直是 Jassy 实施成本削减的目标，在过去的一年里，整个公司已经裁掉了大约 27,000 个工作岗位。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-835256?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">亚马逊设备主管 David Limp 于 2018 年在西雅图展示 Amazon Echo Sub 低音炮。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：安德鲁·伯顿/彭博新闻</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>Limp 的退出计划标志着亚马逊高层领导核心（即 S 团队）的又一次混乱，在 Jassy 掌​​舵之前，管理团队相对稳定，S 团队的一些成员在过去两年中已经离职。</p><p>亚马逊发言人证实林普将于今年年底前离职。</p><p>据《华尔街日报》此前报道，去年，亚马逊消费者首席执行官戴夫·克拉克 (Dave Clark) 在任职 23 年后离开了公司，部分原因是<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/andy-jassy-amazon-bezos-overexpansion-11655383388?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">与贾西亲力亲为的管理风格发生冲突</a>。自 2021 年中期以来，S 团队的其他离职人员包括领导<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/amazon-executive-who-oversaw-entertainment-push-exits-company-11670006169?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">媒体和娱乐业务的</a>杰夫·布莱克本 (Jeff Blackburn)； Alicia Boler Davis， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/alicia-boler-davis-alto-pharmacy-11671834987?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">全球客户履行</a>高级副总裁；查理·贝尔，亚马逊云业务最高领导人；杰伊·卡尼 (Jay Carney) 是<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/amazon-public-policy-executive-jay-carney-leaving-tech-giant-for-airbnb-11658506003?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">公共关系和公共政策的最高主管</a>。</p><p>林普现年 56 岁，于 2010 年加入亚马逊运营其设备，他于 20 世纪 80 年代末在<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/AAPL" class="company-name">苹果</a>公司开始了自己的职业生涯，随后又在其他几家公司工作过， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/palm-ceo-carl-yankowski-had-big-plans-for-a-pocket-size-computer-92528ada?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">其中包括 Palm</a> ，这是智能手机之前的个人数字助理领先品牌组织。</p><p>当时，该公司该部门唯一的畅销产品是 Kindle 电子阅读器。在他任职期间，亚马逊推出了包括Echo智能音箱、Fire TV流媒体播放器和Fire平板电脑在内的多款热门产品。它还推出了一款命运多舛的智能手机，名为<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/amazon-curtails-development-of-consumer-devices-1440632203?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">Fire 手机</a>，但后来停产了。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=525FE8E5-82DD-4B5F-BFDE-5A465613584C&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Famazons-leader-on-alexa-echo-and-other-devices-plans-to-leave-cde4f689&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption"> The line between Amazon and Walmart is becoming increasingly blurred, as the two companies seek to maintain their slice of the estimated $5 trillion retail market while chipping away at the other&#39;s share, often by borrowing the other&#39;s ideas. Photos: Amazon/Walmart. (Published April 2022)<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>尽管亚马逊已售出超过 5 亿台支持 Alexa 的设备，但智能音箱的销售基本上每台设备都没有盈利。 《华尔街日报》去年报道称，该设备部门近年来的<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/amazon-has-launched-a-cost-cutting-review-focused-on-unprofitable-business-units-11668094823?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">年运营亏损超过 50 亿美元</a>。</p><p>林普部门战略的一部分是销售刺激亚马逊其他销售的产品，但在这一努力上取得了不同程度的成功。该部门的首款产品 Kindle 就是该战略发挥作用的一个例子，因为它推动了电子书的销售，而亚马逊从中分一杯羹。</p><p>在 Echo 设备系列中，该公司高估了客户对语音购物的采用率（即人们告诉 Alexa 他们想从亚马逊购买商品），这仍然只占客户使用 Echo 设备方式的一小部分。</p><p>通过 Echo 设备投放广告也具有挑战性，因为用户会对广告感到沮丧，尤其是在他们在设备上听音乐的时候。大多数客户使用他们的设备执行简单的命令，例如要求其设置计时器或天气预报，而这两者都不能让亚马逊赚钱。</p><p>写信给 Dana Mattioli <a href="mailto:dana.mattioli@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">（dana.mattioli@wsj.com）</a>和 Jessica Toonkel（ <a href="mailto:jessica.toonkel@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">jessica.toonkel@wsj.com</a> ）</p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 14 Aug 2023 20:04:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/amazons-leader-on-alexa-echo-and-other-devices-plans-to-leave-cde4f689</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/amazons-leader-on-alexa-echo-and-other-devices-plans-to-leave-cde4f689<author><![CDATA[Dana MattioliJessica Toonkel]]></author><category> WSJ公司</category><category>专有的</category><category>零售批发</category><category>伊泰林</category><category>电子商务</category><category>在线服务提供商</category><category>零售</category><category>技术</category><category>企业战略/规划</category><category>管理</category><category>管理层变动</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>高层管理人员</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>亚马逊网站</category><category>亚马逊</category><category>大卫·林普</category><category>企业战略</category><category>规划</category><category>管理</category><category>管理举措</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>高层管理人员<